text.tspan: The term percent means per hundred, or hundredths. Percents are ratios that are often used to

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal; font-family: 'Courier new'; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: represent parts of a whole, where the whole is considered as having 100 parts.

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 40px; line-height: normal; font-family: 'Courier new'; cursor: pointer;

text.tspan: 1 percent means 1 part out of 100 parts, or 1/100

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal; font-family: 'Courier new'; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: 50 percent means 50 parts out of 100 parts, or 50/100 or 1/2

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal; font-family: 'Courier new'; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: To compute a percent, given the part and the whole, divide the part by the whole.

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal; font-family: 'Courier new'; cursor: pointer; fill-opacity: 1;
text.tspan: The result will be the decimal equivalent, so multiply the result by 100 to convert to percent.

text.tspan: If the whole is 20 and the part is 15, you can find the percent as follows
